title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.7 EMERGENCIES

description.narrative: Output 1.7: Government and partner institutions are prepared, have adequate sectoral capacity and provide an effective and coordinated response for Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH), nutrition and health in emergencies., which contributes to Child Health, Health And Emergencies, Maternal And Newborn Health, Nutrition And Emergencies, Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Wash And Emergencies. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: Women and children have more equitable access to evidence-based health, nutrition, Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) and HIV services and adopt appropriate care practices from pregnancy to adolescence.

description.narrative: UNICEF supported;GOI’s;COVID-19 response at national and sub-national levels through WASH supplies, technical assistance for IPC, disinfection and hygiene protocols and strengthening WASH Cluster coordination. In the transitional phase, UNICEF is strengthening;governments’ capacity for rehabilitation planning processes, sustainability of WASH services and hygiene behaviors in high-risk and vulnerable populations. Ensuring sustainability of essential maternal newborn and child health services remains a priority in the health sector. UNICEF works, in close partnership with GOI and other development partners to ensure essential health services are well-provided and well-received by children and mothers in all regions of Indonesia during COVID-19;pandemic. | Status:Met | As-of Date:24/11/2020
